  "html": "<div class=\"fr-view\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91); font-size: 16px; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif;\">Day 31</span></p><ul><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use of たform + り to express a list of actions - Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on the expression in たform＋あとで - Lesson 2, 3</span></span></span></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Different use of particle を and に - Lesson 2&nbsp;</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Three new kanji: 時, 分, 半</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 32</span></span></span></p><ul><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verbs in ないform &nbsp;- Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on verbal form ないでください&nbsp;- Lesson 2</span></span></span></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use of the particle は - Lesson 1, 2</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Katakana for vegetables and fruits</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 33</span></span></span></p><ul><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on なければなりません &nbsp;- Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use of までに&nbsp;- Lesson 1</span></span></span></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on なくてもいいです - Lesson 2</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Three new kanji: 国, 火, 水</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 34</span></span></span></p><ul><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on verbs in plain form &nbsp;- Lesson 1, 2, 3</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on verbs in plain form + けど - Lesson 2</span></span></span></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use of the particle で - Lesson 3</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Katakana for entertainment and leisure words</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 35</span></span></span></p><ul><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verb in plain form + と思います &nbsp;- Lesson 1, 2</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on the particles と - Lesson 1, 2, 3</span></span></span></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on the particles について - Lesson 2</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verb in plain form + と思っています - Lesson 3</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Three new kanji: 金, 土, 年</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 36</span></span></span></p><ul><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verb in plain form + と言いました - Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verb in てform ＋きます - Lesson 2</span></span></span></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Three new kanji: 書, 友, 休&nbsp;</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 37</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on the particle が and の - Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on the structure N1は+noun modifier+N2です - Lesson 1, 2</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verb in てform+います &nbsp;- Lesson 2</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on the structure N1は+noun modifier+N2をVます - Lesson 3</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on the structure Noun modifier+Nは〜 - Lesson 4</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Katakana for things around me</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 38</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verb in plain form+ら - Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on the particles が and に (used as へ) - Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verb in たform+ら &nbsp;- Lesson 2</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Counting up to １億 (one billion)</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Three new kanji: 今, 週, 校</span></span></span></p></li></ul></div><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 39</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use 〜てもform - Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use 〜なくてもform - Lesson 2</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use a plain style in informal conversations &nbsp;- Lesson 3</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Katakana for seasoning</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 40</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use of いAdjectiveく／なAdjectiveに／Nounになります - Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on the particles に - Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verb in dictionary form+と &nbsp;- Lesson 2, 3</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on the particle と - Lesson 2</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on the particle を - Lesson 3</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Three new kanji: 前, 午, 後</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 41</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use of the verb in ～てform + あげます&nbsp;- Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use of the verb in ～てform + もらいます&nbsp;- Lesson 2</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Three new kanji: &nbsp;読, 見, 聞</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 42</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use of the pattern N1(人)にN2をくれます&nbsp;- Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;Grammar focus on が &nbsp;- Lesson 2</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use of the pattern N(人)にV(て形)くれます &nbsp;- Lesson 3</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">More katakana for sports <br></span></span></span></p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-si