dana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;Use of よね at the end of a sentence &nbsp;- Lesson 3</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">More katakana for things in the room&nbsp;</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 45</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use of the verb in present and past form + とき - Lesson 1, 2, 3</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use the noun+は+といういみです&nbsp;- Lesson 4</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;Use of the verb in plain form + といっていました &nbsp;- Lesson 4</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Three new kanji: 兄, 姉, 弟</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 46</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">use question words + verb in plain form + か&nbsp;- Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verb in plain form + かどうか&nbsp;- Lesson 2</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;Verb in てform + みます &nbsp;- Lesson 3</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;Three new kanji: 妹, 家, 族</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 47</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verbs in potential form&nbsp;- Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on the use of the particles しか&nbsp;- Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on the use of the particles は and も&nbsp;- Lesson 2</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">More katakana for countries&nbsp;</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 48</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use the verb in plain form + んです - Lesson 1, 2, 3, 4</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Three new kanji: 男, 女, 春</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 49</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use a verb in plain form +ですが&nbsp;- Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on が &nbsp;- Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">use a verb in plain form + でしょう &nbsp;- Lesson 2</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on けど and なお - Lesson 3</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">More katakana for stationery words&nbsp;</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 50</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use a question word + verb in た form + らいいですか&nbsp;- Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use of たらform + どうですか &nbsp;- Lesson 2</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use of the particle ずつ &nbsp;- Lesson 2</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verb in て form + いただけませんか&nbsp;- Lesson 3</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Three new kanji: 夏, 秋, 冬</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 51</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Use of verb in plain form + し、verb in plain form + し - Lesson 1, 2, 3</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Three new kanji: 朝, 昼, 夜</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 52</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verb in ます form + ながら + another verb in ます - Lesson 1, 2</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on ながら &nbsp;- Lesson 1, 2</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-