verb in た form + まま + another verb in ます form - Lesson&nbsp;1</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">verb in plain form + んじゃないですか&nbsp;- Lesson 2</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">use the verb in plain form + かな - Lesson 3</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">More katakana for countries&nbsp;</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 58</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verb in the ます form + ましょうか - Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verb in intentional form - Lesson&nbsp;2</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verb in intentional form + と思っています&nbsp;- Lesson 3</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Three more kanji: 古, 長, 店</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 59</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">verb in dictionary form or a noun + ために - Lesson 1, 2</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Focus on everyday conversation - Lesson 3</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">More katakana for things that are around me&nbsp;</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Day 60</span></span></span></p><ul><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Verb in plain form + のは +～だ - Lesson 1</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">Grammar focus on the use of の - Lesson 1, 2, 3</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;Use the verb in plain form + を+ 忘れます / 知ってます - Lesson 3</span></span></span></p></li><li><p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91); font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">&nbsp;Three more kanji: 駅, 電, 話</span></p></li></ul>",
